============================================================
  FAMOUS PEOPLE
============================================================

Name:          Tim Berners-Lee
Lived:         1955 - present
Nationality:   English
Field:         Computing
Known For:     World Wide Web
Contribution:  Invented the Web in 1989; gave it to the world for free
Quote:         "The web does not just connect machines, it connects people."

Name:          Alan Turing
Lived:         1912 - 1954
Nationality:   English
Field:         Computing
Known For:     Turing machine, codebreaking
Contribution:  Father of computer science; broke Enigma; Turing test for AI
Quote:         "We can only see a short distance ahead, but we can see plenty there that needs to be done."

Name:          Nelson Mandela
Lived:         1918 - 2013
Nationality:   South African
Field:         Politics
Known For:     End of apartheid
Contribution:  First democratically elected SA president; 27 years in prison; Nobel Peace Prize
Quote:         "Education is the most powerful weapon you can use to change the world."

============================================================
  PHILOSOPHY
============================================================

Concept:      Empiricism
Branch:       Epistemology
Definition:   All knowledge comes from sensory experience; mind is blank slate
Philosopher:  Locke/Hume
Example:      We know fire burns because we felt it, not through pure reason

Concept:      Utilitarianism
Branch:       Ethics
Definition:   Maximize pleasure minimize pain across all sentient beings
Philosopher:  Jeremy Bentham
Example:      Felicific calculus: measure units of pleasure and pain

Concept:      Phenomenology
Branch:       Epistemology
Definition:   Philosophy must study first-person conscious experience directly
Philosopher:  Husserl/Heidegger
Example:      What is the structure of my experience of time or other people?

============================================================
  SCIENCE FACTS
============================================================

Domain:  Mathematics
Topic:   Central Limit Theorem
Formula: Sample means → normal distribution
Note:    Foundation of statistical inference and polling

Domain:  Physics
Topic:   Planck's Constant
Formula: h = 6.626×10⁻³⁴ J·s
Note:    Quantum of action; E = hf for photon energy

Domain:  Astronomy
Topic:   Milky Way Size
Formula: ~100,000 light-years diameter
Note:    Our galaxy; contains 200-400 billion stars

Domain:  Biology
Topic:   Cell Theory
Formula: All life is made of cells arising from pre-existing cells
Note:    Foundation of modern biology

Domain:  Physics
Topic:   Newton's Second Law
Formula: F = ma
Note:    Force equals mass times acceleration; classical mechanics

